WEBVTT

00:01.480 --> 00:03.210
Okay, five Newtonian
equations down.

00:03.210 --> 00:04.890
Only seven quantum mechanical
proofs to go!

00:05.660 --> 00:06.930
We are cooking
with C-H-4.

00:07.770 --> 00:10.640
Ohh! [ Laughs ]
Cooking with gas.

00:10.640 --> 00:12.610
And they're both single, fellas.

00:12.610 --> 00:14.810
Come on, guys.
Can't we just have one day

00:14.810 --> 00:17.040
where we respect and support
one another?

00:17.040 --> 00:17.800
Hello, family.

00:17.810 --> 00:18.940
[ Chuckles ]

00:20.120 --> 00:21.150
There was an incident
this morning

00:21.220 --> 00:22.740
at our annual neighborhood
block party.

00:22.900 --> 00:25.640
Cam usually provides the
entertainment at these things,

00:25.640 --> 00:28.310
but he had Lily's birthday
party, so Phil volunteered.

00:28.310 --> 00:30.510
Who needs a Fizbo
if you can have a Philbo?

00:30.510 --> 00:32.009
What?!

00:32.490 --> 00:33.990
I mean, where does it end?

00:34.040 --> 00:36.110
It's so long!
It's comically long,

00:36.110 --> 00:37.480
when you think about it.

00:37.480 --> 00:39.880
Thing is,
Phil's terrified of clowns.

00:39.880 --> 00:43.150
Just thought if I was the clown,
I wouldn't be scared.

00:43.150 --> 00:45.450
Like how you can't
tickle yourself.

00:45.450 --> 00:47.210
[ Sebastian laughing ]

00:47.220 --> 00:48.060
Sebastian, no!

00:48.060 --> 00:50.450
I got this!
Sebastian!

00:50.460 --> 00:51.890
Your mom's worried
about you, buddy,

00:51.890 --> 00:53.720
even though there's absolutely
no reason to be...

00:53.730 --> 00:56.700
[ Gasps, breathing heavily ]

00:56.700 --> 00:58.830
Smell... oh, God.

00:58.830 --> 01:01.990
[ Labored breathing ]

01:02.000 --> 01:04.360
S-s-s-clowns!

01:04.370 --> 01:05.660
Honey.

01:05.670 --> 01:08.730
[ Moaning ]
They were everywhere.

01:08.740 --> 01:11.700
I recognize that I embarrassed
the family this morning,

01:11.710 --> 01:13.210
but I assure you that...

01:13.210 --> 01:16.380
Phil, honey, just come on
over here for one second.

01:16.380 --> 01:17.810
Just a sec.

01:17.820 --> 01:21.490
Honey, you are not the first
person to put on a clown outfit,

01:21.490 --> 01:23.890
walk into
a hall of mirrors, and...

01:23.890 --> 01:25.860
I guess what I'm saying is

01:25.860 --> 01:29.770
if you think you need to do
something to make up for that,

01:29.770 --> 01:31.060
<i>don't</i> think that.

01:31.060 --> 01:32.060
- No!
- [ Gasps ]

01:32.070 --> 01:33.340
Oh, my God, the computer froze!

01:33.340 --> 01:34.660
- Daddy to the rescue!
- Um...

01:34.670 --> 01:35.940
Well,<i> I</i> feel heard.

01:35.940 --> 01:37.610
Yeah, you know what, Dad,
I-I think it's okay.

01:37.600 --> 01:38.900
I just need to do
a hard reset...

01:38.910 --> 01:40.280
No, I don't think
it's a reset issue.

01:40.280 --> 01:42.570
I think the surge protector
just blew.

01:42.580 --> 01:47.450
I am going to plug this bad boy
directly into the wall and...

01:47.450 --> 01:49.120
[ Thunder crashes,
electricity zaps ]

01:49.120 --> 01:50.690
Oh, my God!
You fried my computer!

01:50.690 --> 01:51.880
All of our work is gone!

01:51.890 --> 01:53.860
Honey, calm down.
These hard drives are designed

01:53.860 --> 01:55.350
to withstand temperatures
of up...

01:55.360 --> 01:57.660
- Aaaah!
- Oh, my God, it's on fire!

02:11.740 --> 02:13.870
Damn it.

02:13.870 --> 02:15.100
What is wrong?

02:15.110 --> 02:17.210
Huh? Nothing.

02:17.210 --> 02:19.750
You know, I totally forgot
some of my Navy buddies

02:19.750 --> 02:21.080
are meeting downtown later

02:21.080 --> 02:23.080
for a little reunion
at O'Brien's pub.

02:23.080 --> 02:25.040
Well, nothing special
is happening here today,

02:25.050 --> 02:26.410
so you have permission to go.

02:26.420 --> 02:27.820
Well, I don't really need
your permission.

02:27.820 --> 02:31.320
Why don't you just keep quiet
and take yes for an answer?

02:31.320 --> 02:35.550
Ay, there's my handsome,
perfect, amazing boy!

02:35.560 --> 02:36.820
Still not going
on the class trip.

02:36.830 --> 02:38.830
Why are you being such a dummy?
Is this because I...

02:38.830 --> 02:40.230
Mom, I don't want
to talk about it.

02:40.230 --> 02:42.230
Why am I the only one
in this house

02:42.240 --> 02:44.400
that ever wants to talk
about things?!

02:44.400 --> 02:45.400
[ Joe crying ]

02:45.410 --> 02:46.840
Ay, papi, what is wrong?

02:46.840 --> 02:48.740
Not now.

02:48.740 --> 02:49.630
[ Crying continues ]

02:49.640 --> 02:50.970
Okay, that's it.

02:50.980 --> 02:53.110
If the men in this house
don't start talking to me,

02:53.110 --> 02:56.070
I swear to God that I will
make life miserable

02:56.080 --> 02:57.410
for each and every one of you!

02:57.420 --> 02:58.620
[ Thunder crashes,
electricity zapping ]

02:58.620 --> 03:00.920
No, not yet.

03:00.920 --> 03:02.760
Oh, don't tell me the power
just went out!

03:02.760 --> 03:04.660
My Sleep Number bed is stuck
on the nap setting.

03:04.660 --> 03:07.260
Calm down. This is exactly why
I sprung for a new generator.

03:07.260 --> 03:08.500
[ Generator powers on ]

03:08.500 --> 03:09.760
Which, you're welcome,
just kicked in.

03:09.760 --> 03:11.620
Now, granted,
it doesn't power everything.

03:11.630 --> 03:13.360
I had to make some hard choices.

03:13.370 --> 03:15.670
Hmm. That's it?
The bar and the pool table?

03:15.670 --> 03:18.040
The frigerator's black.

03:18.040 --> 03:19.370
Okay, Jay, you're not leaving

03:19.370 --> 03:21.470
until you put power
in the important things.

03:21.470 --> 03:24.100
I swear to God, don't make me
more mad than I already am!

03:24.110 --> 03:25.450
Can't I just do it
when I get back?

03:25.450 --> 03:26.520
[ Thunder crashes ]

03:26.520 --> 03:28.170
Would you stop doing that?!

03:29.980 --> 03:31.440
It's Lily's 8th birthday,

03:31.450 --> 03:33.980
and we had a little
backyard party planned.

03:33.990 --> 03:35.520
Hot dogs, some balloons...

03:35.520 --> 03:37.850
You know, I mean, we really
just threw it together.

03:37.860 --> 03:39.730
Kind of like my birthday party
last year.

03:39.730 --> 03:42.330
Okay, you told me that you did
not want me to do anything...

03:42.330 --> 03:44.530
Anyway, we were all set
for a casual kids' party,

03:44.530 --> 03:46.630
but then [voice breaking]
Lily got an e-mail.

03:46.630 --> 03:48.830
She's coming! She's coming!
She's coming! Ashley's coming!

03:48.840 --> 03:50.240
[ Gasps ]
Ashley's coming?

03:50.240 --> 03:51.710
Mitchell, Ashley's coming!

03:51.710 --> 03:53.230
Oh, my God!
Well, now, wait a minute.

03:53.240 --> 03:54.710
Ashley S. or Ashley W.?

03:54.710 --> 03:55.880
"W"!
[ Gasps ]

03:55.880 --> 03:58.980
ALL:
Ashley W.'s coming!

03:58.980 --> 04:01.380
Ashley is the most popular girl
in Lily's class.

04:01.380 --> 04:03.010
I mean, you invite her...
Yeah.

04:03.020 --> 04:04.880
But you never think
she's gonna accept.

04:04.880 --> 04:06.580
No. Something must have fallen
through, or...

04:06.590 --> 04:08.760
The point is, she decides
who's in and who's out.

04:08.760 --> 04:10.230
So we had to up our game.

04:10.230 --> 04:11.380
Which was a fun challenge.

04:11.390 --> 04:13.080
Yeah, considering
it had been a while

04:13.090 --> 04:15.490
since we'd thrown any sort of
fabulous birthday party.

04:15.500 --> 04:17.500
You begged me not to make
a fuss. You said...

04:17.500 --> 04:19.200
Oh, because that sounds
like me, yeah.

04:19.200 --> 04:20.740
All right.
Once Sophie boards the bus,

04:20.740 --> 04:23.060
we will be on our way
to the Princess Park,

04:23.070 --> 04:26.110
where we will all pick out
our princess costumes!

04:26.110 --> 04:27.570
[ Girls chatting ]

04:27.570 --> 04:29.730
I think Ashley's having
a really good time.

04:29.740 --> 04:31.270
Yeah?
How can you tell?

04:31.280 --> 04:32.380
She's still here.

04:32.380 --> 04:33.520
[ Thunder crashes,
girls scream ]

04:33.510 --> 04:34.340
Oh!

04:34.350 --> 04:35.450
Oh, no!
Is it raining?

04:35.450 --> 04:37.120
Not to worry, sweetie.
We have parasols.

04:37.120 --> 04:38.380
[ Wind gusts ]
Oh!

04:38.380 --> 04:39.040
Oh...

04:39.050 --> 04:40.350
It worked!

04:40.350 --> 04:42.180
Good. I powered up
all your essentials.

04:42.190 --> 04:43.760
Now I'm gonna go meet
my buddies.

04:43.760 --> 04:45.890
I see my espresso machine
didn't make the cut,

04:45.890 --> 04:47.190
but I'll manage.

04:47.190 --> 04:49.350
One of the guys I'm meeting
was lost at sea once.

04:49.360 --> 04:50.390
Had to eat a jellyfish.

04:50.400 --> 04:52.130
I'll speak to him
of your courage.

04:54.100 --> 04:57.470
So, power's out.
Had to come over real quick.

04:57.470 --> 04:58.770
Phil got dressed up as a clown

04:58.770 --> 05:00.470
and then had a panic attack
in a hall of mirrors,

05:00.470 --> 05:02.470
so he's gonna be looking to
overcompensate for a lot,

05:02.480 --> 05:03.910
so please don't indulge
in any of his...

05:03.910 --> 05:04.910
- Hey, Jay.
- Right here.

05:04.910 --> 05:06.070
I remembered you had
a generator.

05:06.080 --> 05:08.480
I'm just gonna upload
a few quick files for Alex.

05:08.480 --> 05:09.540
Don't ask.

05:09.550 --> 05:10.720
I never do.

05:10.720 --> 05:12.450
I can't open the jar.

05:12.450 --> 05:15.380
Well, lucky for you
your uncle...

05:15.390 --> 05:17.390
Brother-in-law Phil
is here.

05:17.390 --> 05:20.560
And with one mighty twi...

05:20.560 --> 05:22.560
We should be...

05:23.900 --> 05:25.730
Bloop! Bloop!

05:25.730 --> 05:26.790
Good to go.

05:26.800 --> 05:28.000
Oh!
- Dad!

05:28.000 --> 05:28.990
- No!
- No, no, no, no, no!

05:29.000 --> 05:30.300
No, no, no!

05:30.300 --> 05:31.730
Dad, stop helping!
Ugh!

05:31.740 --> 05:33.070
Hey, monster.

05:33.070 --> 05:35.230
Hey, you.

05:36.180 --> 05:38.310
Andy I started out
pretty hot and heavy,

05:38.310 --> 05:40.910
but, uh, the last few weeks
I've just been super busy,

05:40.910 --> 05:42.740
so I guess he's feeling
neglected,

05:42.750 --> 05:44.150
and he's acting a little cold.

05:44.150 --> 05:45.450
I mean, a chuck on the arm?

05:45.450 --> 05:47.410
What are we,
Huck Finn and Tom Sawyer?

05:47.420 --> 05:49.160
[ Chuckles ]

05:49.160 --> 05:50.590
Those are people, right?

05:50.590 --> 05:52.630
[ Water trickling ]

05:52.630 --> 05:53.690
[ Gasps ]

05:53.690 --> 05:55.090
Ay, there's a puddle!

05:55.090 --> 05:56.250
Stella or Joe.

05:56.260 --> 05:57.290
I'll see you
in a couple of hours.

05:57.300 --> 05:58.670
No, no, no, no!
Look, it's a leak,

05:58.670 --> 06:00.300
because it's coming
through the wall.

06:00.300 --> 06:02.270
Most likely
your gutters backed up.

06:02.270 --> 06:03.340
Consider it handled.

06:03.340 --> 06:04.870
Please don't ask me.
Please don't ask me.

06:04.870 --> 06:06.030
Luke!
To the gutters!

06:06.040 --> 06:08.210
[ Sighs ]

06:08.210 --> 06:10.140
[ Girls chattering ]

06:10.140 --> 06:12.200
Okay, princesses,
your castle awaits!

06:12.210 --> 06:13.470
What gives?

06:13.480 --> 06:14.880
The roads were starting
to flood,

06:14.880 --> 06:16.710
so we were hoping to ride out
the storm here.

06:16.720 --> 06:18.050
Yeah, sure.

06:18.050 --> 06:20.450
Also, Dad, we're hoping to keep
the princess theme alive,

06:20.450 --> 06:21.780
so if you could pretend
to be a...

06:21.790 --> 06:23.790
Interested?
No.

06:23.790 --> 06:25.160
- [ Sighs ]
- Okay.

06:25.160 --> 06:26.800
Ladies, it's costume time!
We have...

06:26.800 --> 06:27.890
GIRL: Costumes!

06:27.890 --> 06:30.290
Belle, we have Elsa,
we have Ariel!

06:30.300 --> 06:32.070
Costumes?

06:32.070 --> 06:34.200
Ew, costumes.

06:34.200 --> 06:35.970
What are we, 5?

06:35.970 --> 06:36.970
Okay.

06:36.970 --> 06:38.640
Uh, okay, so, that's happening.

06:38.640 --> 06:39.740
Hey, Ashley hates the costumes.

06:39.740 --> 06:41.010
You got to think
of something else!

06:41.010 --> 06:43.040
What do we do?
Well, I don't know.

06:43.040 --> 06:45.040
Our friends are basically
8-year-old girls.

06:45.040 --> 06:46.500
What would <i> they</i> want to do?

06:46.510 --> 06:48.140
BOTH: Dance party!

06:48.150 --> 06:50.350
Yeah? Yeah?
Okay. Okay, girls.

06:50.350 --> 06:52.420
Uh, let's get some music started
here, huh?

06:52.420 --> 06:54.590
Oh. Oh, God, Cam,
there's no power.

06:54.590 --> 06:56.060
There's Cam power.

06:56.060 --> 06:57.590
What...?

06:57.590 --> 06:58.860
What is that?

06:58.860 --> 07:01.530
Well, had I listened to you
and we not donated to NPR,

07:01.530 --> 07:04.060
we wouldn't have gotten
this free emergency radio

07:04.060 --> 07:05.690
that we then re-gifted
to Jay and Gloria.

07:05.700 --> 07:08.400
I wouldn't call $19 a month
free, but okay.

07:08.400 --> 07:11.660
All right, let's get a little
funk in here, ladies!

07:11.670 --> 07:12.860
[ Groans ]

07:12.870 --> 07:14.230
♪<i> She's a brick</i> ♪

07:14.240 --> 07:15.270
Oooh!

07:15.270 --> 07:16.400
♪<i> House</i> ♪

07:16.410 --> 07:17.710
[ Radio powers down, dies ]
Okay.

07:17.710 --> 07:19.950
[ Cranking ]
Little more funky energy
in this thing!

07:19.950 --> 07:21.180
Got to warm up, you know?

07:21.180 --> 07:22.850
Got to get it warmed up!

07:22.850 --> 07:25.520
♪<i> She's mighty, mighty,</i>
<i>just le...</i> ♪

07:25.520 --> 07:26.520
[ Radio powers down, dies ]

07:26.520 --> 07:27.790
I don't know what's wrong
with me.

07:27.790 --> 07:29.020
This is my
butter-churning arm.

07:29.020 --> 07:30.650
[ Grunts ]

07:31.860 --> 07:33.890
Third drawer from the left.

07:33.890 --> 07:35.720
I have no idea what
you're talking about.

07:35.730 --> 07:38.730
Thank you.
What's with the robe?

07:38.730 --> 07:40.960
I had to go outside and cover
my drought-resistant garden.

07:40.970 --> 07:42.400
Timing, right?

07:42.400 --> 07:44.260
Well, anyway, there's no power
in my room,

07:44.270 --> 07:46.410
and I wasn't gonna get dressed
in the dark, so...

07:46.410 --> 07:48.340
Ohh!
Oh, no!

07:53.310 --> 07:54.640
How crazy is your dad, huh?!

07:54.650 --> 07:56.320
Braving the elements!

07:56.320 --> 07:59.890
Keeping the family dry!
That is fur!

07:59.890 --> 08:01.550
[ Banging ]

08:01.550 --> 08:03.480
What's the plan, Luke?

08:03.490 --> 08:04.960
There are no bad ideas,

08:04.960 --> 08:08.130
but waving a metal shovel around
in an electrical storm

08:08.130 --> 08:09.460
could have a downside,

08:09.460 --> 08:11.460
so let's put it back
in the garage, huh?

08:11.460 --> 08:12.460
[ Thunder crashes ]

08:12.470 --> 08:13.740
Whoa, that was close!

08:13.740 --> 08:15.130
[ Clatter ]

08:15.130 --> 08:17.400
Oh, my God!
Not again!

08:17.400 --> 08:18.400
[ Girls chattering ]

08:18.400 --> 08:19.960
Oh, honey, you're gonna be fine.

08:19.970 --> 08:21.970
I can't believe you let him
get struck again!

08:21.970 --> 08:23.230
Again?

08:23.240 --> 08:25.400
Don't worry about it, champ.

08:25.410 --> 08:26.740
I don't even think it hit him.

08:26.750 --> 08:28.320
Last time he smelled
like aluminum.

08:28.320 --> 08:29.570
Last time?!

08:29.580 --> 08:32.580
Honey, your father and I
are trying to talk.

08:32.590 --> 08:34.419
Okay, everyone.

08:34.419 --> 08:36.620
Don't feel like you have to wait
for me to get back.

08:36.620 --> 08:38.080
GLORIA: Jay!

08:38.090 --> 08:40.090
The leak is growing!

08:40.090 --> 08:41.320
I was just on my way back out.

08:41.330 --> 08:42.500
- I'll do it.
- But...

08:42.500 --> 08:43.200
Sit!

08:43.200 --> 08:45.700
[ Door closes ]

08:45.700 --> 08:48.000
That's a silly excuse not
to go to your school trip.

08:48.000 --> 08:50.100
Mom, I've made my decision.

08:50.100 --> 08:52.460
Oh. Hey.

08:52.470 --> 08:53.870
Hey.

08:53.870 --> 08:55.200
What's going on here?

08:55.210 --> 08:57.710
I could cut the tension
with my machete.

08:57.710 --> 08:59.680
It's so... nothing.

08:59.680 --> 09:01.880
I mean [scoffs]
Manny got his robe

09:01.880 --> 09:03.210
caught in the refrigerator door,

09:03.220 --> 09:05.490
and I may have
accidentally seen...

09:05.490 --> 09:06.540
him.

09:06.550 --> 09:08.050
Oh, you <i> saw.</i>

09:08.050 --> 09:09.210
Okay.

09:09.220 --> 09:11.380
Manny, it's over.
What happened happened.

09:11.390 --> 09:12.390
It's done.
Okay?

09:12.390 --> 09:14.390
Okay, good,
because I have a problem

09:14.390 --> 09:16.050
and I need your help, Claire.

09:16.060 --> 09:17.560
Yes. You got it.
What is it?

09:17.560 --> 09:20.160
Well, Manny doesn't want to go
to his school trip

09:20.170 --> 09:21.470
because there is a rumor

09:21.470 --> 09:23.670
that the kids want to go
skinny-dipping,

09:23.670 --> 09:25.810
and he's self-conscious
about his body.

09:25.810 --> 09:28.840
I'm gonna pretend
I don't understand

09:28.840 --> 09:30.640
why you're including me
in this conversation.

09:30.640 --> 09:31.970
I'm just saying...

09:31.980 --> 09:34.220
You could tell him
since you already peeped.

09:34.220 --> 09:35.370
I didn't peep.

09:35.380 --> 09:37.310
Tell him that he has
a beautiful body

09:37.320 --> 09:40.190
so at least something good
comes out of the peeping.

09:40.190 --> 09:41.660
Please stop saying that.

09:41.660 --> 09:43.750
When I see Luke naked,
I am going to tell him,

09:43.760 --> 09:46.060
"Luke, you have
a beautiful body."

09:46.060 --> 09:47.330
"When"?

09:47.330 --> 09:48.930
Maybe she doesn't think
I have a beautiful body.

09:48.930 --> 09:50.030
Ohh.

09:50.030 --> 09:52.070
IAy, dios mío!
Claire, is this true?

09:52.070 --> 09:53.390
No!
Okay, I can't do this.

09:53.400 --> 09:55.670
I'm... I'm just gonna go ahead
and walk away now.

09:55.670 --> 09:58.270
But if a bolt of lightning
should strike this house,

09:58.270 --> 10:00.200
you can send it <i> my</i> way.

10:00.210 --> 10:01.670
Oh! Oh!

10:01.670 --> 10:03.330
[ Girls chattering ]
[ Sighs ] Okay.

10:03.340 --> 10:05.940
What... they didn't like
the peanut-butter sandwiches?

10:05.950 --> 10:08.180
No. No one would touch them
after Ashley said,

10:08.180 --> 10:09.250
[As Ashley] "Crunchy?"

10:09.250 --> 10:11.050
Sh! What are you, crazy?
She's right there.

10:11.050 --> 10:12.550
Ugh!
This is ridiculous.

10:12.550 --> 10:15.010
Are we really gonna let an
8-year-old dictate this party?

10:15.020 --> 10:16.550
You know how peer pressure is.

10:16.560 --> 10:18.390
I had an Ashley
when I was Lily's age.

10:18.390 --> 10:20.790
She blackballed me
from the cafeteria table,

10:20.790 --> 10:22.550
and then no one
would sit with me.

10:22.560 --> 10:25.760
I had to eat outside
with the class rooster.

10:25.770 --> 10:27.300
And then one day...

10:27.300 --> 10:28.730
Okay, if this ends
in another case

10:28.730 --> 10:30.190
of you almost eating one of
your animal friends, I can't.

10:30.200 --> 10:32.060
But... okay. This is... this is
what I'm gonna do.

10:32.070 --> 10:33.400
If we get Ashley on board,

10:33.410 --> 10:35.580
everything else will just fall
into place.

10:35.580 --> 10:37.900
I convince juries that
guilty people are innocent.

10:37.910 --> 10:39.710
I can certainly convince Ashley

10:39.710 --> 10:41.210
that our party ideas are dope.

10:41.210 --> 10:42.210
[ Mouth full ] Yeah,
but don't say dope.

10:42.210 --> 10:43.470
I won't say dope.

10:43.480 --> 10:46.240
Ugh. Hey, Ash.
[ Chuckles ]

10:46.250 --> 10:47.710
So, listen.

10:47.720 --> 10:48.720
Oops.

10:48.720 --> 10:50.050
Oh, gosh.
Oh, good call.

10:50.060 --> 10:52.730
Um, I'm thinking about kicking
this party up a notch,

10:52.730 --> 10:53.730
more grown-up activi...

10:53.730 --> 10:55.060
Uh, i-i-it's still...

10:55.060 --> 10:56.720
Yeah. Yes, it is.
My word.

10:56.730 --> 10:58.230
Kind of a tweener on sizes.

10:58.230 --> 11:00.400
And we always tend to go
smaller, don't we?

11:00.400 --> 11:02.170
I mean, human nature,
am I right?

11:03.840 --> 11:06.910
Anyway, um, a lot
of high-school girls

11:06.910 --> 11:09.740
are really just falling in love
with Pictionary,

11:09.740 --> 11:13.070
and I sort of... um, uh...
Oh, gosh.

11:13.080 --> 11:16.750
Cam bought me this shirt,
and I...

11:16.750 --> 11:18.950
can't believe I just tried
to blame Cam.

11:18.950 --> 11:22.450
Mitchell, take responsibility...
You eat bread, you billow.

11:22.460 --> 11:23.690
Anyway...
[ Cellphone rings ]

11:23.690 --> 11:24.690
your shirt is really nice,
and I...

11:24.690 --> 11:26.360
- Hey.
- Yeah. Take the call.

11:26.360 --> 11:27.690
Nobody.

11:27.690 --> 11:29.020
[ Voice cracking ]
Bye, Ash.

11:29.030 --> 11:31.630
[ Gasps ]
Hey, sexy!

11:31.630 --> 11:33.370
What's all this?

11:33.370 --> 11:37.470
Oh, just a little something
special for <i> you</i> and <i> I.</i>

11:37.470 --> 11:38.540
I would put those away.

11:38.540 --> 11:40.610
Joe goes crazy if you play
with his blocks.

11:40.610 --> 11:43.110
Maybe it's time for us
to get a little crazy.

11:43.110 --> 11:44.510
Come here.

11:45.710 --> 11:47.610
I was afraid of this.

11:47.610 --> 11:50.810
This is why I was trying to slow
things down with Haley.

11:50.820 --> 11:54.050
Women are always drawn
to me physically

11:54.050 --> 11:56.680
in a <i> very</i> intense way.

11:56.690 --> 11:58.230
Which often fizzles out

11:58.230 --> 12:01.390
before we have a chance
to connect emotionally.

12:01.390 --> 12:02.550
So...

12:02.560 --> 12:03.690
Yes?

12:03.700 --> 12:05.570
There are so many
things about you

12:05.570 --> 12:07.290
that I just don't know.

12:07.300 --> 12:11.040
I feel, in the Book of Haley,
I'm only in chapter one.

12:11.040 --> 12:13.210
Turn the page for me, girl.

12:13.210 --> 12:14.540
What?

12:14.540 --> 12:17.150
Would it help you to open up
if I were to brush your hair?

12:17.150 --> 12:19.540
You mean in a hot way?

12:19.550 --> 12:22.820
I got us some wine.

12:22.820 --> 12:24.190
You know what would be better?

12:24.190 --> 12:27.310
Two cups of soothing green tea

12:27.320 --> 12:29.420
to warm our emotional
availability.

12:29.420 --> 12:32.220
Ooh, the places we will go.
I'll be right back.

12:32.220 --> 12:34.850
HALEY: I hope this doesn't
sound conceited,

12:34.860 --> 12:36.600
but <i> everyone</i> wants me.

12:36.600 --> 12:38.570
I just knew there had to be
a rational reason

12:38.570 --> 12:40.160
Andy was rejecting me.

12:41.730 --> 12:43.900
Beth's Coast Guard uniform.

12:43.900 --> 12:45.560
I can't believe
he's not over her.

12:45.570 --> 12:46.500
She's a size six!

12:46.510 --> 12:48.680
Hey!
Who moved my blocks?!

12:50.210 --> 12:53.550
Okay, so, Vi equals 367 meters
per second,

12:53.550 --> 12:55.220
and D equals .00214,
so th...

12:55.220 --> 12:57.840
Alex, did you know I was struck
by lightning?

12:57.850 --> 12:59.690
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.
Not right now. Maisie, continue.

12:59.690 --> 13:01.250
Uh... I lost it.

13:01.250 --> 13:02.710
[ Groans ]

13:02.720 --> 13:05.550
So... can we talk
about my thing now?

13:05.560 --> 13:06.790
Okay, look, you're really hot,

13:06.790 --> 13:08.120
and under the right
circumstances,

13:08.130 --> 13:09.800
I could see myself making out
with you, but...

13:09.800 --> 13:10.700
Ew.

13:10.700 --> 13:12.060
But we're trying
to re-create

13:12.060 --> 13:14.390
all the work that we lost on the
computer this morning, so...

13:14.400 --> 13:16.040
Also, every time
you open your mouth,

13:16.040 --> 13:18.070
you let out a cloud of stupid
over the entire room.

13:18.070 --> 13:19.540
Wow. [ Scoffs ]

13:19.540 --> 13:21.880
I don't want to be in here
with you losers anyway.

13:21.880 --> 13:23.300
And another thing...

13:23.310 --> 13:24.580
Can we circle back
to what Maisie just said?

13:24.580 --> 13:25.580
Get out!

13:27.910 --> 13:30.070
- Hey. Back already?
- Never left.

13:30.080 --> 13:31.540
And now the pool's a centimeter

13:31.550 --> 13:33.220
from overflowing
right in the house.

13:33.220 --> 13:34.220
I got to pump the pool.

13:34.220 --> 13:35.560
Wait, wait, wait, wait!

13:35.560 --> 13:37.050
Jay, I want you in that bar,

13:37.060 --> 13:38.890
and I need to feel like a man.

13:38.890 --> 13:40.590
Let me pump your pool.

13:40.590 --> 13:41.920
All right. One hose in the pool,
the other one...

13:41.930 --> 13:43.260
Jay, shh.
It's me.

13:43.260 --> 13:44.390
You're right.
I'll do it.

13:44.400 --> 13:46.070
No, no, no, no, no.
I got it. I got it.

13:46.070 --> 13:48.070
Gloria, I'll be back
in a couple hours!

13:48.070 --> 13:51.440
What the... Son of a bitch!
Who left the door open?!

13:51.440 --> 13:53.240
Stella!
Stella!

13:53.240 --> 13:54.310
She probably got outside.

13:54.310 --> 13:55.740
Who the hell
left the door open?!

13:55.740 --> 13:56.730
Not me!

13:56.740 --> 13:57.400
Nope.

13:57.410 --> 13:58.740
Oh, God.

13:58.740 --> 13:59.570
What have I done?

13:59.580 --> 14:01.080
JAY: Stella!
Stella?

14:01.080 --> 14:03.350
All set, here, Jay!
Working like a charm!

14:03.350 --> 14:04.750
Admit it!

14:04.750 --> 14:06.490
You didn't think I could
actually... Aaah!

14:06.490 --> 14:08.520
Aaah!
[ Grunts ]

14:14.790 --> 14:15.450
Oh, no, no, no.
What are you doing?

14:15.460 --> 14:16.850
What are you doing?

14:16.860 --> 14:18.360
Wha... well, Phil had this
in his trunk...
[ Sighs ]

14:18.360 --> 14:19.360
and I didn't have
faith in your "talk to
Ashley" plan, so...

14:19.370 --> 14:20.940
So you decided to go
with Bleeding Clown?

14:20.930 --> 14:22.330
Well, how did your talk
with Ashley go?

14:22.330 --> 14:23.860
It...
Is your shirt stapled?

14:23.870 --> 14:25.640
Yea...
Don't worry about it.

14:25.640 --> 14:28.180
Okay, I will not have
our daughter eat lunch

14:28.180 --> 14:30.200
with a rooster
for the next year.

14:30.210 --> 14:33.050
We have a fully-licensed clown
right here.

14:33.050 --> 14:38.220
And I defy any child to not be
delighted by that!

14:38.220 --> 14:39.490
A clown.

14:39.490 --> 14:40.620
You don't like clowns?

14:40.620 --> 14:41.820
Please.

14:41.820 --> 14:43.490
You know what?

14:43.490 --> 14:44.720
Shut up, Ashley!

14:44.720 --> 14:45.780
[ All gasp ]

14:45.790 --> 14:47.950
GLORIA: Jay! Jay.

14:47.960 --> 14:50.700
The water is coming inside
the house from the pool!

14:50.700 --> 14:51.830
Of course it is.

14:51.830 --> 14:54.040
Because Phil was supposed
to pump it out!

14:54.040 --> 14:55.630
Actually,
there's an emergency valve.

14:55.630 --> 14:57.360
PHIL: At the north end of
the pool. I know that valve.

14:57.370 --> 14:58.540
I'm gonna open that valve.

14:58.540 --> 14:59.870
Haven't you done enough already?

14:59.870 --> 15:01.570
Please!
I need this!

15:01.570 --> 15:03.470
And who else would dare to jump

15:03.480 --> 15:05.410
in that pool right now anyway?

15:06.810 --> 15:07.870
Me!

15:07.880 --> 15:09.680
I'm not sure
about the rest of you,

15:09.680 --> 15:12.880
but I'm going swimming,
in the rain, in my clothes!

15:12.890 --> 15:15.550
TOGETHER: Pool party!

15:15.550 --> 15:16.880
I am not gonna...

15:16.890 --> 15:18.320
Can I come?

15:18.320 --> 15:19.350
Um...

15:19.360 --> 15:20.390
Do whatever you want, Ashley.

15:20.390 --> 15:21.920
Yeah.

15:21.930 --> 15:24.400
Is she following?
Don't look back.

15:24.400 --> 15:26.470
[ Girls laughing, squealing ]

15:30.400 --> 15:32.530
Everybody stand back!

15:32.540 --> 15:33.870
I opened the valve!

15:33.870 --> 15:35.000
[ Girls chant "Lily!" ]

15:35.010 --> 15:36.680
I'm happy for her.

15:36.680 --> 15:37.950
[ Chanting continues ]

15:37.950 --> 15:39.540
Your husband's
outside half naked.

15:39.550 --> 15:41.220
There's still time
to go downstairs

15:41.220 --> 15:42.710
and body shame him if you like.

15:42.720 --> 15:45.120
Okay. Let's you and me get this
over with.

15:46.720 --> 15:48.090
Huh.

15:48.090 --> 15:49.190
[ Door slams ]

15:50.560 --> 15:52.890
Okay, you're really putting
on mixed signals here.

15:52.890 --> 15:54.550
Please stop talking.
Okay.

15:54.560 --> 15:56.960
Of course you're insecure
about your body.

15:56.960 --> 15:57.960
You're a teenager.

15:57.960 --> 15:59.790
It's part of the job
description.

15:59.800 --> 16:02.740
But if this whole skinny-dipping
thing ever even happens,

16:02.740 --> 16:05.070
you have nothing to worry about.

16:05.070 --> 16:06.910
- Easy for you to...
- You're still talking.

16:06.910 --> 16:08.380
You have nothing to worry about

16:08.380 --> 16:10.300
because nobody's going to be
looking at you,

16:10.310 --> 16:12.080
because all those other kids

16:12.080 --> 16:15.120
are gonna be too preoccupied
with their own insecurities.

16:15.120 --> 16:16.770
But i-if they do?

16:16.780 --> 16:18.580
[ Inhales sharply, sighs ]

16:18.580 --> 16:19.810
You'll be fine.

16:19.820 --> 16:23.920
You're the most confident kid
I have ever met,

16:23.920 --> 16:25.780
and that is always sexy.

16:25.790 --> 16:29.050
Thanks, Claire.

16:29.060 --> 16:31.260
Mm.

16:31.260 --> 16:32.760
And if this helps you
in any way,

16:32.770 --> 16:34.240
I've always found you sexy, too.

16:34.240 --> 16:36.890
Super.

16:36.900 --> 16:38.560
Oh, God.

16:39.610 --> 16:40.980
[ Straining ]

16:43.810 --> 16:45.910
Stop pouting!

16:45.910 --> 16:47.000
That's so not you.

16:47.010 --> 16:49.410
Who cares that you dressed up
as a clown,

16:49.420 --> 16:51.590
then scared yourself
in many mirrors?

16:51.590 --> 16:53.240
Actually, what's even
more embarrassing

16:53.250 --> 16:55.010
is that I thought if I ran
into that fun house

16:55.020 --> 16:55.960
and grabbed that kid,

16:55.960 --> 16:57.110
everyone would look at me

16:57.120 --> 16:58.650
like the hero I always
wanted to be.

16:58.660 --> 17:00.190
Correction.
What's most embarrassing

17:00.190 --> 17:01.620
is everything I've done
since then

17:01.630 --> 17:03.200
to try to make up
for the first thing.

17:03.200 --> 17:05.700
What are you talking about?
"Hero"?

17:05.700 --> 17:07.700
You're so much more than that.

17:07.700 --> 17:08.700
You have flaws.

17:08.700 --> 17:10.030
You fall down a lot.

17:10.040 --> 17:11.440
You frighten yourself.

17:11.440 --> 17:14.470
You cannot even open a jar.
You cry all the time.

17:14.470 --> 17:16.270
I'm really ready for this
to build into a compliment.

17:16.280 --> 17:19.210
The point is that you are
comfortable with yourself,

17:19.210 --> 17:21.970
and you make people around you
feel comfortable.

17:21.980 --> 17:24.220
They feel that they
can talk to you.

17:24.220 --> 17:25.980
That's your superpower!

17:25.980 --> 17:29.810
Pool's drained, leaks are fixed,
generator's running,

17:29.820 --> 17:30.980
and I'm meeting my buddies.

17:30.990 --> 17:32.560
Why, Jay?
Why you have to go out?

17:32.560 --> 17:33.730
It's a hurricane outside!

17:33.730 --> 17:34.830
I just do.

17:34.830 --> 17:35.960
[ Lid rattles ]

17:37.460 --> 17:39.460
I think you probably
loosened it with the...

17:39.470 --> 17:41.030
Don't.

17:41.030 --> 17:43.630
Here's your precious uniform!

17:44.300 --> 17:45.500
That's Beth's.

17:45.500 --> 17:47.570
Oh, so you admit you're still
in love with her!

17:47.570 --> 17:48.170
What?

17:48.170 --> 17:49.200
Ow!

17:49.210 --> 17:50.980
Just saying "Hey."
Hurts, doesn't it?

17:53.410 --> 17:54.870
Haley!

17:54.880 --> 17:56.380
Haley!

17:56.380 --> 17:57.910
Stop!
What are you doing?

17:57.920 --> 17:59.750
You won't kiss me.
You won't even touch me.

17:59.750 --> 18:01.180
And then I find Beth's uniform?

18:01.190 --> 18:02.160
So you tell me, okay?

18:02.160 --> 18:03.410
What do you do with it anyway?

18:03.420 --> 18:05.220
You... you... you sniff it,
you snuggle it,

18:05.220 --> 18:07.220
you put it on a coat rack
and dance with it?!

18:07.230 --> 18:09.330
I'm sending Beth's things
back to her,

18:09.330 --> 18:12.230
and I got her uniform pressed
because I love my country.

18:12.230 --> 18:14.190
So, y-you and Beth, you...

18:14.200 --> 18:16.540
There is no Beth.
There's only you.

18:16.540 --> 18:18.570
I'm just trying to
slow us down a little.

18:18.570 --> 18:21.040
We kind of started this whole
thing off in the middle.

18:21.040 --> 18:23.180
I just want us to
catch up emotionally

18:23.180 --> 18:26.040
to where we are physically
so we don't burn out.

18:26.040 --> 18:27.170
We're not going to burn out.

18:27.180 --> 18:28.720
I liked you way before
we ever hooked up.

18:28.720 --> 18:32.540
I just want our relationship
to be as good as our affair.

18:32.550 --> 18:35.880
I mean, we never even had
a romantic first date.

18:35.890 --> 18:38.890
[ Chuckles ]
I know.

18:38.890 --> 18:41.890
Maybe we should wait
for the perfect moment

18:41.890 --> 18:43.720
so we can start
our relationship right.

18:43.730 --> 18:47.230
Something special and magical,
like in the movies.

18:47.230 --> 18:48.730
[ Laughing ] What do
you want me to do,

18:48.730 --> 18:50.030
chase you through an airport?

18:50.040 --> 18:51.400
I think we got it.

18:51.400 --> 18:54.800
Oh, yeah.
[ Chuckles ]

19:00.480 --> 19:02.650
Come on!

19:02.650 --> 19:04.750
A damn tree's blocking
the street.

19:04.750 --> 19:05.920
I need my chainsaw.

19:05.920 --> 19:08.450
Jay, I know you didn't ask
my advice...

19:08.450 --> 19:10.550
I'm glad you noticed that.
I've been stuck here all day.

19:10.560 --> 19:11.720
Now, I'm going to that bar!

19:11.720 --> 19:13.250
The last thing I need's
another delay.

19:13.260 --> 19:14.600
Where the hell's the chainsaw?!

19:14.600 --> 19:15.920
It's right there.

19:15.930 --> 19:18.060
[ Thunder crashes ]

19:18.060 --> 19:19.460
[ Sighs ]

19:21.930 --> 19:23.890
I'm not gonna get there, am I?

19:23.900 --> 19:26.000
We don't have to talk about it.

19:26.000 --> 19:30.940
Old Navy buddy of mine,
Big Jake, died today.

19:30.940 --> 19:33.670
Guys in my unit have a tradition

19:33.680 --> 19:37.320
whereas, when one of us goes,
the rest of us,

19:37.320 --> 19:41.650
no matter where we are,
find the nearest Irish pub,

19:41.650 --> 19:46.920
and at 7:00,
silently toast the fallen.

19:48.930 --> 19:51.960
Started with 10 guys.

19:51.960 --> 19:54.830
Four of us left.

19:54.830 --> 19:56.860
Probably should have told
Gloria about it,

19:56.870 --> 19:57.810
but I don't know.

19:57.810 --> 19:59.000
We...

19:59.000 --> 20:01.930
We all went through
some rough stuff together...

20:04.340 --> 20:06.340
Hard to talk about.

20:08.350 --> 20:09.880
[ Sighs ]

20:25.630 --> 20:26.960
[ Cup clinks ]

20:26.970 --> 20:28.570
Thanks.

20:31.070 --> 20:32.370
Phil.

20:33.970 --> 20:35.430
[ Cup clinks ]

20:42.150 --> 20:43.980
[ Cups clink ]

20:57.000 --> 20:58.400
Why can't we remember
this last piece?

20:58.400 --> 21:00.070
We just had it this morning.

21:00.070 --> 21:01.330
Hey, guys.
I know you're busy,

21:01.330 --> 21:02.830
but do you think being hit
by lightning

21:02.830 --> 21:03.690
can make people smarter?

21:03.700 --> 21:04.930
Get out of here.

21:04.940 --> 21:07.340
Huh.

21:07.340 --> 21:08.740
What...

21:08.740 --> 21:10.610
Yeah.
It's probably just a myth.

21:10.610 --> 21:11.950
There's so much crazy stuff

21:11.950 --> 21:13.900
written on the Internet
these days.

21:13.910 --> 21:15.940
Turns out, when they figured it
out the first time,

21:15.950 --> 21:18.090
the formula was in the
background of a selfie I took.

21:18.090 --> 21:19.340
[ Chuckles ]

21:19.350 --> 21:21.610
Anyway, if you don't think
lightning can do that,

21:21.620 --> 21:23.060
it must not be true.

21:23.060 --> 21:26.090
After all, you are the smartest
people I know.

21:26.090 --> 21:27.380
[ Marker thuds ]

21:27.390 --> 21:29.090
[ Thunder crashes ]
